# Game Management and Launching Fixes

I have completed the UI improvements, Epic Games fixes, and the robust launch targeting system for all game sources.

## Changes Made

### UI & Drivers
- **Redundant Button Removed**: Removed the `+` button from the Graphics settings tab as requested.
- **Contextual Installation**: The `+` button in the Components Manager now intelligently installs the correct wrapper (DXVK, VKD3D, Wine/Proton, Box64, etc.) based on the active tab.
- **Improved Visibility**: Added an "Installed" filter chip to the Drivers section to easily view all installed drivers.

### Epic Games & Amazon Fixes
- **Executable Detection**: Improved the heuristic for finding Epic and Amazon executables, filtering out common crash-handlers and redistributables.
- **Working Directory**: Ensured games start in their own directory to resolve file-loading crashes.

### Game Launch Targeting
- **Robust Steam Targeting**: Updated `ColdClientLoader` to use direct `A:\` drive paths. This bypasses symlink naming issues and resolves the "Couldn't find the requested Exe file" error.
- **Settings Persistence**: Fixed a bug where user-selected Steam executables were not being saved correctly due to an internal ID mismatch.
- **Enhanced Debug Logging**: Added detailed logs to all launch paths (Steam, Epic, Amazon, GOG, Custom) showing the final command and working directory.

